		{
			"type": "action",
			"name": "Manifest Fear",
			"system": {
				"actionType": {
					"value": "action"
				},
				"description": {
					"value": "<p>The Mula targets a creature within 30 feet from it that it can see, invading their mind with frightful images. Target creature must attempt at a @Check[will|dc:31] Save or take @Damage[4d12[mental]] damage. Once used, the mula can't use Manifest Fear again for [[/gmr 1d4 #Duration]]{1d4 rounds}.</p><hr /><p><strong>Critical Success</strong>: Target creature is unaffected.</p><p><strong>Success</strong> Target creature takes half damage and it's @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.TBSHQspnbcqxsmjL]{Frightened 1}.</p><p><strong>Failure</strong> Target creature takes full damage and is @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.TBSHQspnbcqxsmjL]{Frightened 2}.</p><p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> as failure but the creature is @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.TBSHQspnbcqxsmjL]{Frightened 3}.</p>",
